 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Indicator of plot-level performance</div>
 <p id="Par20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Because tree growth and mortality are determinants of forest population dynamics
  <span class="sup">
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR60" href="#CR60">60</a>,
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR68" href="#CR68">68</a>
  </span>, they can be used to characterise its ecosystem state in response to extreme climate events when recruitment is controlled for. For each measurement period 
  <span class="italic">t</span> from 2001 to 2017, we use DBH of each tree to construct its stem basal area increment and then sum all trees in a plot 
  <span class="italic">P</span>. This basal area growth rate for plot 
  <span class="italic">P</span> at time 
  <span class="italic">t</span>, 
  <span class="italic">BAGR</span>
  <sub>
   <span class="italic">P</span>,
   <span class="italic">t</span>
  </sub> (in cm²), is an indicator of plot-level performance:
  <div id="Equ2" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">2</span>
   <div class="alternatives">
    <span id="M5" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$${{\rm{B}}{\rm{A}}{\rm{G}}{\rm{R}}}_{P,t}=\frac{1}{{\rm{\Delta }}t}\sum _{i=1}^{{\rm{N}}{\rm{o}}.\,{\rm{t}}{\rm{r}}{\rm{e}}{\rm{e}}{\rm{s}}\,{\rm{i}}{\rm{n}}\,{\rm{p}}{\rm{l}}{\rm{o}}{\rm{t}}\,{\rm{P}}\,}\,\sum _{j=1}^{{\rm{N}}{\rm{o}}.\,{\rm{o}}{\rm{f}}\,{\rm{s}}{\rm{t}}{\rm{e}}{\rm{m}}{\rm{s}}}(\frac{\pi {{\rm{D}}{\rm{B}}{\rm{H}}}_{P,i,j,t}^{2}}{4}-\frac{\pi {{\rm{D}}{\rm{B}}{\rm{H}}}_{P,i,j,t-{\rm{\Delta }}t}^{2}}{4})$$\end{document}</span>
